x201t-wacomd is a small FreeBSD userspace bridge for the internal serial
Wacom ISDv4 pen digitizer in the Lenovo ThinkPad X201 Tablet.

It reads ISDv4 pen packets from the tablet serial device, typically
/dev/cuau2 at 19200 baud, and can expose the tablet through /dev/uinput for
Xorg or through /dev/consolectl for FreeBSD tty console pointer support.

The XORG port option installs the xf86-input-wacom runtime dependency and the
Xorg InputClass sample. Disable that option for console-only installations on
systems without Xorg.
